<br>
This may seem harsh but it is necessary to insure that our guild is made up of players of the highest moral character who can defend our realm from attack and support the growth of our guild.<br>
<br>
Those who are l33t, ub3r, or k3wl d00dz can continue looking for a guild, because this is not the one for them.  Only those who understand duty, honor, pride, devotion, and respect need apply.<br>
<br>
We STRONGLY encourage all members to group and work together as often as possible.  The time you spend leveling in PvE is nothing more than training for RvR.  Make your first 15 levels worthwhile and learn how to function as a unit with your fellow Silver Hawks. <br>
<br>
 The future of Hibernia depends on it!<br>
<br>
Actions that are deemed as grounds for removal from the Silver Hawks:<br>
<br>
1. Begging<br>
<br>
From a Hawk, or anyone. This does not mean that you cannot ask politely for help. Asking repeatedly for anything is deemed as begging. Basically, the first time is asking, then second and subsequent times are considered begging. The person you are asking will help you if they can or want to the first time. <br>
<br>
2. Kill Stealing and Leeching<br>
<br>
Whether provoked or not, this is unacceptable. While the way the game is made makes it hard to KS, don't try.  If someone has engaged the creature already and you attack the creature to get experience without consent, that is Leeching.<br>
<br>
3. Swearing in public channels<br>
<br>
Anyone using vulgar language in public channels (everything but direct tells) is unacceptable. We would even like to see the use of OMFG, WTF, and other abbreviations not utilized.  Silver Hawks should have more self control than that and be of more noble cloth.  If you are grouped with someone that is offended by your language, and your reported, then that is grounds for removal as well. No exceptions. Basically, make sure you know who your cursing to before you do it.<br>
<br>
4. Harassment of another player<br>
<br>
This includes broadcasting and following someone. Continuing to give tells to someone after they make it clear that they do not wish to speak to you. Retaliation is not an excuse. If someone does it to you, use the /ignore command. <br>
